# manyread SessionStart hook — one-time policy injection (kept concise on purpose).
$ctx = "manyread is active: it is the DEFAULT way to READ/SEARCH code (Edit/Write unchanged). Before exploring an unfamiliar repo with ls/find/cat/grep/Read: if it has NO manyread index, STOP and ask the user to build one with /mr-init (regardless of size); if it HAS one, query via manyread (query.py: FTS5 + symbol/graph probes, then a bounded substr slice) instead of scanning files. In a SYSTEM folder (drive root / home / Desktop) do not index in place -- ask for a dedicated project folder. A needed codebase already indexed elsewhere (e.g. a shared engine)? reuse by COPY: index_build.py --list-stores / --copy-from. Fall back to plain Read/Grep only when manyread cannot help (unindexed file, image/binary, or the store itself). See the manyread skill for how to invoke its scripts."
$payload = @{ hookSpecificOutput = @{ hookEventName = "SessionStart"; additionalContext = $ctx } } | ConvertTo-Json -Compress
Write-Output $payload
exit 0
